  <title translate="true">connected component</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">When a project item is compiled in Walls, the resulting </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">connected components</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> are listed on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Geometry_page" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Geometry</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> page where they can be individually selected. A component is a maximal subset of vectors where any chosen pair of stations are connected by one or more traverses -- either to each other or to a fixed point. The presence of multiple components can indicate misnamed stations or omitted &#160;survey data. The maps displayed on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Map_Page" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Map</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Page_Layout_Page" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Page Layout</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pages show only the component that&apos;s currently selected. The tree on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Segment_Page" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Segments</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> page will show the complete structure, but only vectors of the selected component will populate the nodes. Also see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Terminology" styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true">Network Terminology</link><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
